docs.abstract: A case brought by Democrats in Congress could give them access to a wide array of financial documents from the president and the Trump Organization.
docs.snippet: A case brought by Democrats in Congress could give them access to a wide array of financial documents from the president and the Trump Organization.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Congressional Democrats cleared a key hurdle on Friday in their effort to sue President Trump over whether he is illegally profiting from business dealings with foreign governments, in a case that could give the lawmakers access to the Trump Organization’s finances.

headline.main: Judge Denies Trump’s Request to Dismiss Emoluments Lawsuit
headline.print_headline: Judge Denies Trump’s Request to Dismiss Foreign Payments Suit

docs.abstract: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos is preparing to propose new sexual misconduct rules that cement the rights of the accused and reduce liability for institutions.
docs.snippet: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos is preparing to propose new sexual misconduct rules that cement the rights of the accused and reduce liability for institutions.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Education Secretary Betsy DeVos is preparing new policies on campus sexual misconduct that would bolster the rights of students accused of assault, harassment or rape, reduce liability for institutions of higher education and encourage schools to provide more support for victims.

headline.main: New U.S. Sexual Misconduct Rules Bolster Rights of Accused and Protect Colleges
headline.print_headline: DeVos Plans to Reshape Sexual Misconduct Rules

docs.abstract: Foreign diplomats and employees of the United Nations, World Bank, NATO and other international organizations must be married for their partners to get a visa.
docs.snippet: Foreign diplomats and employees of the United Nations, World Bank, NATO and other international organizations must be married for their partners to get a visa.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration will no longer issue family visas to same-sex domestic partners of foreign diplomats or employees of international organizations who work in the United States, State Department officials said on Tuesday.

headline.main: U.S. Bans Diplomatic Visas for Foreign Same-Sex Domestic Partners
headline.print_headline: U.S. Is Ending Diplomatic Visas for Foreign Same-Sex Domestic Partners

docs.abstract: After weeks of not directly attacking Christine Blasey Ford, the president and his Republican allies have embarked on a more aggressive effort to challenge her credibility.
docs.snippet: After weeks of not directly attacking Christine Blasey Ford, the president and his Republican allies have embarked on a more aggressive effort to challenge her credibility.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For more than two weeks he held back. Against all his instincts, President Trump for the most part resisted directly attacking the woman whose sexual assault allegation has jeopardized his Supreme Court nomination. The accuser was to be treated with kid gloves, like “a Fabergé egg,” as one adviser put it.

headline.main: In Risky Shift, Trump and G.O.P. Directly Assail Christine Blasey Ford
headline.print_headline: In Risky Shift, President  And G.O.P. Slam Accuser

docs.abstract: The White House cited “erratic” behavior by Mr. Brennan, who has frequently been a fierce critic of the president.
docs.snippet: The White House cited “erratic” behavior by Mr. Brennan, who has frequently been a fierce critic of the president.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — John O. Brennan, the C.I.A. director under President Barack Obama, struck back at President Trump on Thursday for revoking his security clearance, calling the president’s claims of “no collusion” with Russia to influence the 2016 election “hogwash” and arguing that the commander in chief was trying to silence anyone who would dare challenge him.

headline.main: Ex-C.I.A. Director John Brennan Strikes Back After Trump Revokes His Security Clearance

docs.abstract: Senator John McCain’s death seemed to be a metaphor for the demise of civility and unity in the Trump era.
docs.snippet: Senator John McCain’s death seemed to be a metaphor for the demise of civility and unity in the Trump era.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As leaders of both political parties and foreign dignitaries publicly mourned John McCain on Sunday, President Trump conspicuously avoided a national moment of tribute to a senator whose death seemed to be its own metaphor for the demise of civility and unity in the Trump era.

headline.main: As a Nation Mourns McCain, Trump Is Conspicuously Absent
headline.print_headline: As Nation Unites to Mourn Senator, Trump Is Conspicuously Absent

docs.abstract: Microsoft was surprised not that recent “spear phishing” attempts had occurred, but that they targeted traditional conservative think tanks. Those groups have been critical of Russia.
docs.snippet: Microsoft was surprised not that recent “spear phishing” attempts had occurred, but that they targeted traditional conservative think tanks. Those groups have been critical of Russia.
docs.lead_paragraph: BOSTON — The Russian military intelligence unit that sought to influence the 2016 election appears to have a new target: conservative American think tanks that have broken with President Trump and are seeking continued sanctions against Moscow, exposing oligarchs or pressing for human rights.

headline.main: New Russian Hacking Targeted Republican Groups, Microsoft Says
headline.print_headline: Russian Hackers Broaden Attacks To Conservatives

docs.abstract: The president alternates between gentle and pointed quizzing of his cabinet secretaries in a ritual with a story line that has become almost comically consistent.
docs.snippet: The president alternates between gentle and pointed quizzing of his cabinet secretaries in a ritual with a story line that has become almost comically consistent.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s cabinet meeting on Thursday began with him calling the vaunted Queen of Soul a former employee. It ended with him musing that things were looking up for American farmers who have been stung by the effects of his trade war.

headline.main: Once Dry Discussions, Cabinet Meetings Are Now Part of the Trump Show
headline.print_headline: Boastful President, Fawning Acolytes And a Great Big Table

docs.abstract: Jakiw Palij, the last known surviving Nazi war crimes suspect on American soil, lived in New York quietly for decades, and his removal handed President Trump a political victory.
docs.snippet: Jakiw Palij, the last known surviving Nazi war crimes suspect on American soil, lived in New York quietly for decades, and his removal handed President Trump a political victory.
docs.lead_paragraph: BERLIN — The Nazi guard lived a quiet life in a racially diverse corner of New York City for decades, having lied on his United States immigration papers in 1949 about the type of work he did during World War II. But on Tuesday, he was deported to Germany, ending a 14-year battle to remove him from American soil.

headline.main: Ex-Nazi Guard in U.S., Now 95, Is Deported to Germany
headline.print_headline: U.S. Deports the Last Nazi Suspect After 14 Years of Trying
